<div type="definition">
<p>TYPICALLY VISIBLE DAMAGE to the BODY, CAUSED by being INJURED.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for an injury is shāng 傷.</p>
<p>2. Chuàng 創 refers very concretely to the wound inflicted, the laceration of the skin.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>外傷</p>
<p>金瘡</p>
<p>瘡傷</p>
<p>傷口</p>
<p>瘡</p>
<p>花</p>
<p>痿</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
